name: Julian Assange
summary: Julian Assange, the founder of WikiLeaks, has made his first public appearances since his release from prison and has spoken out about his detention and conviction. The Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe held a hearing in Strasbourg to discuss the chilling effects of Assange's case on human rights. Assange has claimed that he "pleaded guilty to journalism" in order to secure his freedom, stating that he chose "freedom over unrealisable justice." He also made his first public appearance in Strasbourg, where he spoke about his experiences. These events follow Assange's release from prison, where he had been held for violating bail conditions in 2019. His case has drawn attention to concerns about freedom of speech and the protection of journalists.

name: PlayStation Network status
summary: The PlayStation Network (PSN) has experienced a major outage, leaving users unable to access online services on their PS5 and PS4 consoles. The outage, which started on Wednesday, August 24th, has affected users globally and has yet to be fully resolved. Sony has confirmed the outage and is working to restore services as soon as possible. The extended outage has highlighted concerns about the potential issues that could arise if a "PS5 Pro" console were released, as it could potentially result in even longer outages due to increased server load.

name: Dikembe Mutombo
summary: Dikembe Mutombo, a legendary NBA Hall of Famer known for his defensive prowess and philanthropic efforts, has passed away at the age of 58 after a valiant battle with brain cancer. Mutombo's death has sent shockwaves through the basketball community, with heartfelt tributes pouring in from players, coaches, and fans worldwide. Remembered as a gentle giant both on and off the court, Mutombo left an indelible mark on the lives of many, not only through his exceptional basketball skills but also through his tireless humanitarian work.

name: Gavin Creel
summary: Gavin Creel, a celebrated Broadway star, passed away at the age of 48. Creel's remarkable performance in "Hello, Dolly!" earned him a prestigious Tony Award. Throughout his career, he graced the stages of Broadway and graced television screens with notable roles in "American Horror Story." Creel's immense talent and captivating personality left a lasting impression on his colleagues, who remembered him for his remarkable kindness and charisma. The entertainment industry and beyond mourn the loss of this extraordinary performer, whose legacy will continue to inspire and touch the hearts of audiences for generations to come.

name: Jimmy Carter
summary: Former US President Jimmy Carter has reached the milestone of 100 years, becoming the first former president to achieve this longevity. Despite his age, Carter remains active in contributing to society, with one of his long-standing missions, Habitat for Humanity, nearing completion. His birthday has been celebrated with well wishes from President Joe Biden and other dignitaries, while former President Donald Trump made a disparaging remark. Carter's legacy as a man of service and a force for good is widely recognized.

name: Harry Perryman
summary: Harry Perryman, a free agent from GWS, has chosen to sign a six-year contract with Collingwood despite interest from Port Adelaide. The decision was influenced by Collingwood's substantial financial offer. Amidst speculation about the future of young talent Levi Ashcroft, rumors have emerged of a potential bid from another club. Meanwhile, Clayton Oliver has reportedly met with a rival club regarding a possible move in 2024. Speculation continues to swirl about trades, with a "highly sought-after star" potentially being part of future deals. The Houston trade request may be complicated by Perryman's recent move to Collingwood.

name: Pete Rose
summary: Pete Rose, baseball's all-time hits leader, has passed away at the age of 83. His legacy is a complex one, forever tainted by his lifetime ban from Major League Baseball for gambling on his own team. Despite his on-field brilliance, Rose's reputation will likely always be clouded by this controversy, leaving a bittersweet legacy for one of baseball's greatest legends.
